1
00:05:37,008 --> 00:05:38,883
Hello?

2
00:05:38,967 --> 00:05:42,800
Ming!
Turn that stinking music down!

3
00:05:42,883 --> 00:05:44,550
Oh, it's you!

4
00:05:44,592 --> 00:05:47,758
Where's my painting? I want my painting.

5
00:05:48,383 --> 00:05:52,258
In the mail? Well, that's original!

6
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:56,883
I have to say, I'm astonished
that you could do it!

7
00:05:56,967 --> 00:06:00,925
The climb! All that schlepping
at your tender age!

8
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:04,592
Anyway, bad news.
The price for the goggles went up.

9
00:06:04,675 --> 00:06:08,383
The Rembrandt's
not gonna cover my expenses.

10
00:06:09,675 --> 00:06:13,842
Under the circumstances,
40 million would be a bargain.

11
00:06:13,925 --> 00:06:20,217
I don't care how you get it.
Just make sure that you get it fast.

12
00:06:20,258 --> 00:06:23,592
Tick-tock... tick-tock.

13
00:06:36,717 --> 00:06:38,883
- Morning, Mr Cruz.
- Morning.

14
00:06:50,758 --> 00:06:57,133
First you insure the art, only to watch it
get clipped a month after the client buys it.

15
00:06:57,217 --> 00:07:00,258
Well, it could become
part of our ad campaign.

16
00:07:00,342 --> 00:07:06,133
I'll remember that when I go upstairs to hear
about my new position in the Toledo office.

17
00:07:06,508 --> 00:07:09,258
I called you at 4.30 this morning.

18
00:07:10,258 --> 00:07:12,300
I was home in bed.

19
00:07:12,383 --> 00:07:14,800
- You didn't pick up.
- I didn't wanna pick up.

20
00:07:14,883 --> 00:07:16,967
You had company.

21
00:07:17,717 --> 00:07:20,758
- He came in the window.
- How romantic.

22
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:23,342
I think that's how he got in.

23
00:07:23,383 --> 00:07:27,883
This was 70 storeys up with smart-glass
windows at 400 pounds a pop.

24
00:07:27,967 --> 00:07:30,217
He rigged something.

25
00:07:32,342 --> 00:07:34,425
And I think it was...

26
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:39,425
- ..telescoping bolts.
- And you know this how?

27
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:42,133
Excuse me.

28
00:07:46,008 --> 00:07:50,008
- You're showing off again.
- Let a thousand flowers bloom.

29
00:07:50,092 --> 00:07:52,508
- Chairman Mao.
- You got it.

30
00:07:53,925 --> 00:07:56,633
He left the window open when he came in.

31
00:07:56,717 --> 00:07:58,967
The draught blew over the flowers.

32
00:07:59,008 --> 00:08:02,508
I'll bet the bolts on that window
have fresh scratches.

33
00:08:02,592 --> 00:08:04,925
- And who do we like for this?
- Guess.

34
00:08:05,050 --> 00:08:06,633
Oh, gee. I wonder.

35
00:08:08,217 --> 00:08:10,258
Indulge me.

36
00:08:10,883 --> 00:08:12,883
Indulge you?

37
00:08:13,758 --> 00:08:17,092
- Bob, may I?
- Oh, yeah, sure. Go ahead.

38
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:23,383
Four weeks ago, when our client
bought the Rembrandt.

39
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:25,842
- See anyone we know?
- No.

40
00:08:26,008 --> 00:08:28,717
No, and neither did anyone else.

41
00:08:33,883 --> 00:08:35,925
Now look again.

42
00:08:36,008 --> 00:08:39,508
You think he marked the buyer
at the auction house.

43
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:42,217
- Right.
- Good work, Bob.

44
00:08:42,342 --> 00:08:48,175
- And let's not forget the calling card.
- Elvis has not left the building.

45
00:08:49,383 --> 00:08:51,342
This is classic Mac, Hector.

46
00:08:51,425 --> 00:08:56,633
In the five years I've known you, you've liked
MacDougal for half the cases we've worked.

47
00:08:56,717 --> 00:08:59,883
- He's the best.
- He's also 60 years old.

48
00:08:59,967 --> 00:09:04,842
He ain't Spiderman any more. He's a rich guy.
He doesn't have to steal a Rembrandt.

49
00:09:04,925 --> 00:09:07,258
You think he steals because he has to?

50
00:09:08,258 --> 00:09:10,300
Keep working.

51
00:09:31,217 --> 00:09:33,175
So you get in here at 7am,

52
00:09:33,258 --> 00:09:38,300
you work until 10, eat lunch alone,
you have no friends at the office...

53
00:09:38,383 --> 00:09:42,550
- Wow, you've been paying attention.
- I'm worried about you.

54
00:09:43,508 --> 00:09:47,925
Maybe I like being alone.
Maybe I'm getting over someone.

55
00:09:48,008 --> 00:09:53,092
Well, they say nothing gets you over
the last one like the next one.

56
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:56,925
Is this your way of asking me out,
Hector? Huh?

57
00:09:57,050 --> 00:10:00,133
Well, um... not if you’re gonna say no.

58
00:10:03,217 --> 00:10:05,008
You may be right.

59
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:11,717
- He was here this week.
- He flew back to London this morning?

60
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:16,133
It might be worth sending someone
over there, see what he's up to.

61
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:20,217
- I know this guy.
- Do you?

62
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:20,967
Sure!

63
00:10:21,050 --> 00:10:25,592
Some years back, when I was at the Bureau,
we sent two guys after him.

64
00:10:25,675 --> 00:10:28,758
I know, I know. They disappeared.
I know the story.

65
00:10:28,842 --> 00:10:32,258
- And these were both good agents.
- They were both men.

66
00:10:32,342 --> 00:10:34,883
What do you have in mind for bait?

67
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:43,008
- The one thing I know he wants.
- Why not the Mona Lisa?

68
00:10:43,092 --> 00:10:45,175
Our guy likes a challenge.

69
00:10:46,342 --> 00:10:48,008
Come on.

70
00:10:48,842 --> 00:10:50,842
I want this back.

71
00:11:16,925 --> 00:11:19,008
Thank you, sir.

72
00:13:17,883 --> 00:13:19,425
God!

73
00:13:24,217 --> 00:13:26,050
Shit!

74
00:13:48,758 --> 00:13:50,008
Rule number one:

75
00:13:50,092 --> 00:13:53,758
Never carry a gun, or you
might be tempted to use it.

76
00:13:53,842 --> 00:13:56,467
- Why are you here?
- To ask some questions.

77
00:13:56,508 --> 00:14:00,092
If I don't like your answers,
you're going out the window.

78
00:14:00,175 --> 00:14:04,425
- Why are you following me?
- I've got a proposition for you.

79
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:08,925
- How do I know that you're not a cop?
- You'll just have to trust me.

80
00:14:09,008 --> 00:14:11,800
Rule number two:
Never trust a naked woman.

81
00:14:11,842 --> 00:14:15,800
I had nothing to sleep in.
Somebody stole my luggage.

82
00:14:15,842 --> 00:14:17,883
Really? I'm shocked.

83
00:14:17,967 --> 00:14:21,300
It's amazing what gets stolen
these days. Your bags...

84
00:14:21,383 --> 00:14:22,717
That Rembrandt.

85
00:14:24,092 --> 00:14:26,050
Indeed. That Rembrandt.

86
00:14:27,425 --> 00:14:30,758
- And this is your proposition?
- Yep.

87
00:14:30,842 --> 00:14:34,592
- I don't think it's for sale.
- It's not. I'm gonna steal it.

88
00:14:34,675 --> 00:14:38,467
From Bedford Palace?
It's rather well guarded.

89
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:43,717
By its own random-access security code,
changed daily, to which I have the key.

90
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,717
- Well, good for you.
- But I need your help.

91
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,675
I can't get in and out.

92
00:14:48,758 --> 00:14:52,342
I've already got a buyer
who'll give me 40 million for it.

93
00:14:52,425 --> 00:14:55,550
I have no reason to believe
a word you've told me.

94
00:14:55,592 --> 00:14:59,425
- But you want to.
- Why is that?

95
00:15:00,925 --> 00:15:03,133
Because you want the mask.

96
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,342
First we try, then we trust.

97
00:15:09,425 --> 00:15:10,925
Meaning what?

98
00:15:11,008 --> 00:15:14,258
Meet me outside the hotel, 9am.
Preferably dressed.

99
00:15:14,342 --> 00:15:19,008
- How do I know you'll be there?
- Oh, I'll be there. And I'm never late.

100
00:15:19,050 --> 00:15:21,300
- Not ever?
- Never.

101
00:15:21,383 --> 00:15:24,800
If I'm late... it's because I'm dead.

102
00:15:24,883 --> 00:15:26,758
Whose hotel? Yours or mine?

103
00:15:28,842 --> 00:15:31,300
Mac?

104
00:15:32,258 --> 00:15:34,300
Mac?

105
00:15:48,758 --> 00:15:50,800
Ah, here we are.

106
00:15:50,883 --> 00:15:53,633
You go straight in there and ask for Haas.

107
00:15:53,675 --> 00:15:55,217
- Haas?
- Lovely fella.

108
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:56,508
Very low-key.

109
00:15:56,592 --> 00:16:01,217
You tell him you want to buy a Qing vase.
The price is £200,000,

110
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:04,217
- which, of course, you won't pay.
- Why not?

111
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:08,050
Because you're going to steal it.
You are a thief, aren't you?

112
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:15,342
Take this card, which is fake.
As he turns to swipe it, you swipe the vase.

113
00:16:16,133 --> 00:16:17,717
OK.

114
00:16:18,008 --> 00:16:20,050
Enjoy. I'll be waiting.

115
00:16:20,092 --> 00:16:22,175
- Ooh!
- Sorry!

116
00:16:39,467 --> 00:16:42,425
- Hello!
- Hi.

117
00:16:43,675 --> 00:16:47,425
- I'm here for the Qing vase.
- I don't know you.

118
00:16:47,508 --> 00:16:49,967
We've never met before. Mac sent me.

119
00:16:51,675 --> 00:16:54,925
- Where's the money?
- Where's the vase?

120
00:17:07,633 --> 00:17:12,175
- OK, show me the real one.
- No, trust me, babe.

121
00:17:12,258 --> 00:17:16,175
This is better than a real one. 200,000.

122
00:17:18,425 --> 00:17:21,133
- What's that?
- It's a credit card.

123
00:17:21,217 --> 00:17:23,258
Yeah. And?

124
00:17:23,342 --> 00:17:25,133
I need the miles.

125
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:30,300
What exactly... do you think this is?

126
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:34,633
- Harrods?
- No, I've never seen rats at Harrods.

127
00:17:34,717 --> 00:17:37,675
You like a joke, don't you?

128
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:38,842
Sure.

129
00:17:39,675 --> 00:17:41,175
How funny is this?

130
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:48,758
I'm sorry.
I made a terrible mistake about the vase.

131
00:17:48,842 --> 00:17:49,967
Too right.

132
00:17:56,383 --> 00:17:58,467
Uh, yeah, I did.

133
00:18:19,175 --> 00:18:23,842
Time's running out.
You can still escape if you’re quick.

134
00:18:23,925 --> 00:18:25,967
Now listen.

135
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:27,675
- Where's the vase?
- I broke it.

136
00:18:27,758 --> 00:18:29,592
- What!
- I'm sorry...

137
00:18:43,675 --> 00:18:45,092
Oh, God!

138
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,467
God bless!

139
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:51,133
The man had a knife.
What was I supposed to do?

140
00:18:51,217 --> 00:18:56,008
- You were supposed to get the damn vase!
- It was a cheap Victorian knockoff!

141
00:19:01,175 --> 00:19:03,967
You missed the point of the entire exercise.

142
00:19:04,883 --> 00:19:06,967
No, I didn't.

143
00:19:07,925 --> 00:19:09,550
Oh. Good.

144
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:11,550
Good girl!

145
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:13,508
- Give it to me.
- What is it?

146
00:19:13,592 --> 00:19:15,508
Give it to me!

147
00:19:15,592 --> 00:19:16,925
What is it?!

148
00:19:17,008 --> 00:19:18,800
Bedford Palace.

149
00:19:18,883 --> 00:19:22,717
The complete plans,
security system, soup to nuts.

150
00:19:38,883 --> 00:19:41,925
Man, look what you've done
to this beautiful car!

151
00:19:42,008 --> 00:19:45,258
Yeah, thank God it's not mine.
Here, some clothes.

152
00:19:45,342 --> 00:19:50,258
- Where are we going? These are my clothes!
- Yes, you have some nice things.

153
00:19:50,342 --> 00:19:54,925
- It was you? You stole my luggage?
- I'm a thief. So sue me.

154
00:19:55,425 --> 00:19:58,467
- And where are we going?
- Up.

155
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:05,675
- Mac, where is my suitcase?
- It's with hotel security.

156
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,217
With what?!

157
00:20:09,717 --> 00:20:11,258
Why?

158
00:20:11,342 --> 00:20:14,758
Well, there was a robbery yesterday
at Cryptonic.

159
00:20:14,842 --> 00:20:20,383
And someone stole five prototype super chips
worth $4 million each.

160
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:24,342
And one of these chips
is inside your suitcase.

161
00:20:24,425 --> 00:20:26,758
- With hotel security.
- Yes.

162
00:20:26,842 --> 00:20:32,258
And one anonymous phone call,
from me, plus the photos...

163
00:20:32,342 --> 00:20:34,967
- What photos?
- Oh, yes.

164
00:20:35,842 --> 00:20:37,258
These.

165
00:20:39,258 --> 00:20:41,383
Who took...?

166
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:47,342
Hey!

167
00:20:47,425 --> 00:20:50,258
- This is entrapment!
- What?

168
00:20:50,342 --> 00:20:54,883
- This is called entrapment!
- Actually, it's called blackmail.

169
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:57,092
Entrapment...

170
00:20:57,133 --> 00:21:00,675
is what cops do to thieves.

171
00:21:01,758 --> 00:21:03,467
You coming?

172
00:21:22,967 --> 00:21:24,925
Almost there.

173
00:21:57,842 --> 00:22:00,383
No lock? No security?

174
00:22:00,508 --> 00:22:03,383
You're not casing the joint already, are you?

175
00:22:03,384 --> 00:22:05,508
This way.

176
00:22:07,050 --> 00:22:09,133
Oh, wow!

177
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:12,425
Shall we?

178
00:22:20,633 --> 00:22:22,467
Oh, my God.

179
00:22:29,758 --> 00:22:32,925
- This is quite a collection.
- Thank you.

180
00:22:33,675 --> 00:22:35,925
Only contemporary art?

181
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:40,008
- You sound surprised.
- No, it's just not what I expected.

182
00:22:40,092 --> 00:22:43,008
Where are the suits of armour
and crossed swords?

183
00:22:43,050 --> 00:22:45,758
Up in the attic. Whiskey?

184
00:22:45,883 --> 00:22:47,967
Sure. I'd love one.

185
00:22:49,383 --> 00:22:50,883
Wow!

186
00:22:52,925 --> 00:22:55,342
Is all this paid for?

187
00:22:55,425 --> 00:22:58,758
- With blood. Cheers.
- To the mask.

188
00:23:02,842 --> 00:23:07,050
- I'll show you to your room.
- Who else do you bring here?

189
00:23:07,967 --> 00:23:09,175
No-one.

190
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:12,175
- That's sad.
- Why?

191
00:23:12,258 --> 00:23:16,175
Well, to have something like this
and not share it with anyone.

192
00:23:16,258 --> 00:23:20,758
I don't need to share it with anyone.
Most people buy art to show it off.

193
00:23:20,842 --> 00:23:23,050
I collect art for me.

194
00:23:23,133 --> 00:23:25,217
Your room's this way.

195
00:23:30,592 --> 00:23:32,717
Good night, then.

196
00:23:33,008 --> 00:23:36,425
- But it's still early.
- Yes, we have an early start.

197
00:23:36,508 --> 00:23:38,592
But I'm not tired!

198
00:23:39,050 --> 00:23:41,300
Where do you sleep?

199
00:23:44,633 --> 00:23:46,008
Why?

200
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:49,217
Just in case I need anything.

201
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:55,258
- May I ask you something?
- Sure.

202
00:23:55,383 --> 00:24:01,133
Has there ever been anyone you couldn't
manipulate, beguile, or seduce?

203
00:24:02,467 --> 00:24:03,508
No.

204
00:24:05,717 --> 00:24:08,217
Why, do I make you uneasy, Mac?

205
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:11,883
No. No, not at all.

206
00:24:12,717 --> 00:24:19,467
In fact, I think now might be a good time
for you and I to, uh... discuss something.

207
00:24:19,842 --> 00:24:22,967
Well, what do you have in mind?

208
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:25,383
The rules.

209
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:27,342
Oh! OK.

210
00:24:27,925 --> 00:24:32,175
In order for there to be
complete trust between thieves,

211
00:24:32,258 --> 00:24:35,092
there can be nothing personal.

212
00:24:39,175 --> 00:24:42,467
A job is a job. You do your part, I do mine.

213
00:24:43,175 --> 00:24:47,175
If one of us thinks about something
other than the task at hand,

214
00:24:47,258 --> 00:24:51,342
we'll either both get caught,
or both get dead.

215
00:24:54,092 --> 00:24:56,342
Good night again.

216
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,008
No...

217
00:25:14,092 --> 00:25:16,800
Nope. No...

218
00:25:17,758 --> 00:25:20,342
No. No.

219
00:25:20,842 --> 00:25:22,008
Nope.

220
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:25,050
- That's the way in.
- That's the lake.

221
00:25:25,133 --> 00:25:30,925
Yes, I know it's the lake, dear. The first duke
dug a tunnel as a back door for his mistress.

222
00:25:31,008 --> 00:25:33,883
100 years later, they flooded the place.

223
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:36,050
OK, so we go underwater.

224
00:25:36,425 --> 00:25:41,758
I go underwater. I steal the mask.
You get a finder's fee of 10%%%.

225
00:25:41,842 --> 00:25:45,383
But I have the code to the mask case, dear.

226
00:25:45,425 --> 00:25:48,133
Which you're now going to give to me.

227
00:25:49,675 --> 00:25:51,175
No!

228
00:25:53,925 --> 00:25:57,842
- Have you been wasting my time?
- Have you been wasting mine?

229
00:26:03,925 --> 00:26:06,633
I'll arrange your return to London.

230
00:26:09,675 --> 00:26:11,925
I'm not who you think I am, Mac.

231
00:26:12,008 --> 00:26:14,300
I hope not, for your sake.

232
00:26:15,842 --> 00:26:17,883
I'm a thief.

233
00:26:17,967 --> 00:26:20,842
So you keep telling me.

234
00:26:22,425 --> 00:26:24,800
I stole the Rembrandt.

235
00:26:26,092 --> 00:26:31,175
- Mac, I stole the Rembrandt!
- And I painted the Sistine Chapel!

236
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:34,092
Come on! Ask me how I did it!

237
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:36,842
- How did you do it?
- I came in from the roof.

238
00:26:36,925 --> 00:26:41,467
I dropped 20 floors down
on a McNeal Descender.

239
00:26:42,133 --> 00:26:45,008
- You must be a hell of a climber.
- I am.

240
00:26:47,925 --> 00:26:49,592
Mm?

241
00:26:51,842 --> 00:26:54,342
I am a hell of a climber!

242
00:26:55,925 --> 00:27:01,717
I am... one... hell of a climber.

243
00:27:01,758 --> 00:27:04,217
But how did you get it out of there?

244
00:27:05,258 --> 00:27:06,925
Now that...

245
00:27:08,050 --> 00:27:09,925
is the most...

246
00:27:09,967 --> 00:27:11,842
beautiful part!

247
00:27:16,383 --> 00:27:17,883
- I mailed it.
- No!

248
00:27:18,467 --> 00:27:21,842
I put it down their own mail chute.

249
00:27:23,008 --> 00:27:25,717
Simple...

250
00:27:26,925 --> 00:27:29,425
effective... safe.

