- Why are Americans always in a hurry?

754
01:26:35,550 --> 01:26:37,592
- Ten seconds in.
- FDZ complete.

755
01:26:37,675 --> 01:26:38,508
Clear.

756
01:26:38,633 --> 01:26:40,717
Approaching... fifteen.

757
01:26:40,758 --> 01:26:42,300
Clear.

758
01:26:42,383 --> 01:26:43,758
- Here we go!
- Clear!

759
01:26:43,800 --> 01:26:45,800
- All clear.
- Ten seconds.

760
01:26:50,342 --> 01:26:54,342
- Five, four, three,
- Three seconds, people.

761
01:26:54,425 --> 01:26:56,175
two, one...

762
01:26:57,508 --> 01:26:58,758
We're clear.

763
01:26:58,842 --> 01:27:00,592
Happy New Year, Malaysia!

764
01:27:00,675 --> 01:27:03,675
- Ten, nine, eight,
- Come on!

765
01:27:03,758 --> 01:27:05,967
seven, six,

766
01:27:06,092 --> 01:27:08,675
five, four, three,

767
01:27:08,758 --> 01:27:09,883
- two,
- Two.

768
01:27:09,967 --> 01:27:12,008
one!

769
01:27:13,800 --> 01:27:16,842
- We did it!
- Happy New Year!

770
01:27:24,967 --> 01:27:26,383
Happy Millennium!

771
01:27:32,300 --> 01:27:33,925
That was perfect.

772
01:27:47,925 --> 01:27:49,675
Ah, Gin...!

773
01:27:52,008 --> 01:27:54,050
The disk!

774
01:27:56,467 --> 01:27:58,675
- Get me the spanner!
- The what?

775
01:27:58,758 --> 01:28:00,258
The wrench!

776
01:28:01,758 --> 01:28:04,300
If they find that disk, we're dead!

777
01:28:04,800 --> 01:28:06,883
The door!

778
01:28:13,342 --> 01:28:15,425
I can't stop it, Mac!

779
01:28:21,550 --> 01:28:24,342
Armed Response Unit, Code Red.

780
01:28:32,217 --> 01:28:34,633
Leave it! Come on!

781
01:28:59,175 --> 01:29:02,175
- Elevator five's on the move, sir.
- Who's in it?

782
01:29:02,925 --> 01:29:05,133
- It's empty.
- No...

783
01:29:05,258 --> 01:29:11,008
I think they're still in it. Look.
They freeze-framed the camera. See?

784
01:29:11,092 --> 01:29:12,383
Shut it down.

785
01:29:15,508 --> 01:29:17,800
There's always a surprise.

786
01:29:20,550 --> 01:29:21,967
Here.

787
01:29:25,550 --> 01:29:28,800
Suspects in the vicinity of floor 50.

788
01:29:28,883 --> 01:29:32,592
OK, Mr Cruz, your friends are rats in a trap.

789
01:29:45,217 --> 01:29:48,217
- Where to?
- Service elevators.

790
01:29:58,508 --> 01:30:00,508
Get out! Out! Out!

791
01:30:05,467 --> 01:30:07,550
Try the stairs.

792
01:30:16,633 --> 01:30:18,258
Get back!

793
01:30:23,467 --> 01:30:25,425
Hang on.

794
01:30:25,508 --> 01:30:27,592
Got a better idea.

795
01:30:35,092 --> 01:30:38,008
Temper, temper, Mr MacDougal.

796
01:30:38,300 --> 01:30:42,717
Confirm suspects on floor 50,
heading south away from the gas.

797
01:30:42,800 --> 01:30:48,842
They'll think we'll try to avoid the gas, so
keep your eyes closed and take a deep breath.

798
01:31:30,883 --> 01:31:32,967
Get back.

799
01:32:03,967 --> 01:32:05,758
Here.

800
01:32:05,883 --> 01:32:08,550
- What's this?
- Plan B pack.

801
01:32:08,633 --> 01:32:11,675
- For what?
- If we need it, I'll tell you.

802
01:32:11,758 --> 01:32:15,633
Now, if we can get across the vent shaft,
we should be OK.

803
01:32:15,717 --> 01:32:17,133
Across where?

804
01:32:18,883 --> 01:32:20,592
There.

805
01:32:27,467 --> 01:32:30,133
Let's go.

806
01:33:03,842 --> 01:33:06,050
OK.

807
01:33:19,217 --> 01:33:20,508
Move it!

808
01:33:40,175 --> 01:33:41,925
Keep moving!

809
01:33:42,633 --> 01:33:44,300
Come on!

810
01:33:56,342 --> 01:33:57,800
Oh, God!

811
01:34:12,633 --> 01:34:14,258
Gin! Watch out!

812
01:34:35,633 --> 01:34:38,592
Gin! We're nearly there! Move it!

813
01:34:39,550 --> 01:34:40,925
Come on!

814
01:35:03,092 --> 01:35:05,133
Oh, God!

815
01:35:15,425 --> 01:35:17,717
Next stop, vent shaft.

816
01:36:01,550 --> 01:36:05,592
Armed police!
Put your hands above your head!

817
01:36:05,675 --> 01:36:10,967
- Do not move. Remain where you are.
- SWAT team to the roof.

818
01:36:11,050 --> 01:36:12,883
SWAT team to the roof.

819
01:36:12,967 --> 01:36:15,050
Let's go, let's go!

820
01:36:15,258 --> 01:36:17,092
Move, move, move!

821
01:36:17,425 --> 01:36:21,550
If you can't feel alive now, you never will.

822
01:36:23,425 --> 01:36:24,342
Go!

823
01:36:25,633 --> 01:36:28,383
Control, we have a clean shot. Do we take it?

824
01:36:28,425 --> 01:36:32,008
- I repeat, do we take it?
- Negative, Team Leader. Negative.

825
01:36:32,092 --> 01:36:35,550
Do you copy?
I want these people alive and kicking.

826
01:36:37,675 --> 01:36:40,175
Go! Get up into the shaft!

827
01:36:50,425 --> 01:36:52,050
Come on!

828
01:36:55,717 --> 01:36:57,175
Now...

829
01:36:58,050 --> 01:37:00,300
- Plan B. Turn around.
- What?

830
01:37:00,383 --> 01:37:02,008
Turn around.

831
01:37:04,842 --> 01:37:08,425
This is a mini-chute.
But it only works for the updraft.

832
01:37:09,758 --> 01:37:15,383
- I'm not going without you. We go together.
- No, no, no, too heavy. We'd drop like stones.

833
01:37:15,925 --> 01:37:18,092
So when will I see you again?

834
01:37:18,175 --> 01:37:20,842
Meet me at 6.30am, Pudu train station.

835
01:37:20,925 --> 01:37:24,217
You'd better be there, OK?
Promise me you'll be there.

836
01:37:24,300 --> 01:37:28,842
I will be there. I'm never late.
If I'm late, it's because I'm dead.

837
01:37:28,925 --> 01:37:30,300
Now,

838
01:37:30,550 --> 01:37:31,967
rip cord.

839
01:37:37,175 --> 01:37:38,217
Ho!

840
01:39:44,842 --> 01:39:46,883
My God! Mac!

841
01:39:46,967 --> 01:39:51,133
Oh, I'm sorry! I'm sorry. Are you all right?

842
01:39:52,508 --> 01:39:53,967
So what's wrong?

843
01:39:54,050 --> 01:39:59,550
Wrong? Nothing's wrong.
Everything is the... way it has to be.

844
01:39:59,633 --> 01:40:01,467
- What?
- Virginia Baker?

845
01:40:01,550 --> 01:40:04,592
- Special Agent Aaron Thibadeaux, FBl.
- Come on!

846
01:40:04,675 --> 01:40:08,800
You're under arrest for grand larceny.
You have the right to remain silent...

847
01:40:08,883 --> 01:40:10,217
Mac?

848
01:40:10,925 --> 01:40:11,967
Mac!

849
01:40:12,050 --> 01:40:14,883
Anything you say can be used
against you in a court of law.

850
01:40:14,967 --> 01:40:18,467
Thanks, Mac. You got your one minute.

851
01:40:30,050 --> 01:40:31,967
You're a cop.

852
01:40:32,550 --> 01:40:35,217
No. Well, not exactly.

853
01:40:35,300 --> 01:40:39,383
Thibadeaux, believe it or not,
is FBl. And two years ago

854
01:40:39,467 --> 01:40:44,592
he caught me and, uh, cut a deal.
The deal was that... I had to deliver you.

855
01:40:46,592 --> 01:40:49,508
They've been onto you for quite a while.

856
01:40:51,133 --> 01:40:54,092
- And Cruz knew, too?
- No, he's just found out.

857
01:40:55,050 --> 01:41:01,092
I don't get it. Why didn't you pick me up
before? What were you waiting for?

858
01:41:01,758 --> 01:41:06,217
Well, at first I, uh... well,
I wanted to see if you could do it.

859
01:41:06,300 --> 01:41:08,008
Bullshit! Come on!

860
01:41:09,050 --> 01:41:11,800
And I wanted to see if I could do it.

861
01:41:13,133 --> 01:41:15,258
Weren't we partners?

862
01:41:15,800 --> 01:41:18,300
I can't believe you'd do this to me.

863
01:41:18,425 --> 01:41:22,050
Well, you'd better believe it! It's all over.

864
01:41:22,133 --> 01:41:26,383
I gave them Greene,
the Rembrandt, the mask,

865
01:41:26,508 --> 01:41:29,342
and the full seven billion.

866
01:41:30,675 --> 01:41:32,925
What do you mean, seven?

867
01:41:33,217 --> 01:41:36,883
So you'll just have to make do with one, hm?

868
01:41:38,467 --> 01:41:43,467
- I thought you said one minute.
- Relax, Hector. He knows what he's doin'.

869
01:41:43,550 --> 01:41:45,842
Now, plan C.

870
01:41:46,217 --> 01:41:50,800
In your pocket, you'll find an envelope.
A passport, visa, money.

871
01:41:51,342 --> 01:41:57,883
Where you go from here is up to you.
And you'll still hold the record... alone.

872
01:41:57,967 --> 01:42:00,508
Mac!

873
01:42:00,967 --> 01:42:06,050
- I don't understand. Why are you doing this?
- Well, believe me,

874
01:42:06,592 --> 01:42:10,008
I was prepared for everything, except you.

875
01:42:15,092 --> 01:42:18,092
Mac! Time's up!

876
01:42:18,758 --> 01:42:20,758
Come with me.

877
01:42:20,842 --> 01:42:22,800
Gin,

878
01:42:23,967 --> 01:42:26,258
your life, it's all ahead of you.

879
01:42:26,342 --> 01:42:29,258
Mine... this is all I've got.

880
01:42:29,342 --> 01:42:31,133
No. You've got me.

881
01:42:33,508 --> 01:42:36,508
You got me.

882
01:42:40,633 --> 01:42:44,550
Listen carefully. In your other pocket...

883
01:42:45,633 --> 01:42:47,717
Let's do it.

884
01:42:53,383 --> 01:42:57,550
- Move and I blow his head off!
- Everybody, just be cool.

885
01:42:57,633 --> 01:43:01,508
- Nobody move! No-one moves, OK?
- Fellas, put your weapons down.

886
01:43:01,592 --> 01:43:06,175
- You, too, Hector! I'll kill him if you move!
- We'll get her at the next stop.

887
01:43:07,133 --> 01:43:09,217
Bye, Mac.

888
01:43:10,217 --> 01:43:13,508
She's headed toward the next station.
Move! Move it!

889
01:43:13,592 --> 01:43:16,508
- No guns! Get out of here!
- Move it! Move it!

890
01:43:42,217 --> 01:43:47,467
You know, I don't know
what just went down here,

891
01:43:47,550 --> 01:43:52,342
but I'm gonna see that you're busted
outta the Bureau for it.

892
01:43:52,425 --> 01:43:56,342
- It ain't over, Mac.
- I believe you.

893
01:44:09,800 --> 01:44:14,550
Well, Mac, this looks like
the end of a terrible friendship.

894
01:44:14,633 --> 01:44:17,175
But you still owe me for today.

895
01:44:19,092 --> 01:44:21,342
I always pay my debts.

896
01:44:22,717 --> 01:44:28,008
Four prototype super chips.
Value: five million dollars each.

897
01:44:37,008 --> 01:44:39,258
Hope she was worth it.

898
01:44:39,967 --> 01:44:42,050
Oh, she was.

899
01:44:42,508 --> 01:44:44,967
I'll be seein' you, Mac.

900
01:44:46,300 --> 01:44:48,383
I don't think so.

901
01:44:53,092 --> 01:44:56,300
OK, Bob, let the people back on the platform.

902
01:44:56,383 --> 01:44:58,467
Bring me a damn car.

903
01:46:09,967 --> 01:46:12,050
How did you do it?

904
01:46:12,133 --> 01:46:16,842
I jumped trains mid-station.
When the train slowed down, I just...

905
01:46:16,925 --> 01:46:20,092
- It was perfect.
- Was it now?

906
01:46:21,842 --> 01:46:25,925
You know what, Mac?
I don't wanna hold the record alone.

907
01:46:26,008 --> 01:46:28,967
- No?
- I need your help on another job.

908
01:46:29,050 --> 01:46:33,967
- The Crown Jewels or something?
- No! Come on, too easy!

909
01:46:34,092 --> 01:46:38,175
I was thinking of... Well...
I know this guy in South Africa.

910
01:46:38,258 --> 01:46:42,758
Diamonds, diamonds, diamonds! The biggest
diamonds you'll ever see in your life!

911
01:46:42,842 --> 01:46:45,383
Have I told you how much I love diamonds?

912
01:46:46,925 --> 01:46:49,092
Mac?

913
01:46:51,717 --> 01:46:53,800
Mac?

914
01:46:55,217 --> 01:46:57,800
- Mac!
- What!

915
01:47:01,633 --> 01:47:03,883
So, what do you think?

916
01:47:04,217 --> 01:47:07,175
- About what?
- About my idea.

917
01:47:09,800 --> 01:47:11,883
It's doable.

918
01:47:15,508 --> 01:47:18,217
- Ohh!
- Oh, I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

